The paper deals with an optimization problem related to graph theory and combinatorial optimization, specifically the traveling salesperson problem with multiple visits. This suggests that it could belong to categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Among these, cs.DS and cs.CG seem the most likely, as the paper involves algorithmic techniques for solving a geometric optimization problem. The other categories are also possible, as the paper deals with complexity analysis and graph theory, but to a lesser extent.
